.TH DEJA 1 "July 2026" "deja 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
deja \- the clipboard time machine
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B deja
.RI [ command ]
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B deja
records everything you copy to a local SQLite database and makes it
searchable from the command line or a GTK4 popup. A background daemon
watches the clipboard, event-driven and windowless: natively via the
Wayland data-control protocol where the compositor ships it, through
the XWayland bridge (GDK/XFixes) on GNOME, or via GDK on plain X11.
All data stays on your machine.
.PP
Running
.B deja
with no command is equivalent to
.BR "deja list" .
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.BR list ", " ls " [\-n \fIN\fR] [\-p]"
Show recent clipboard history. \-p lists pinned entries only.
.TP
.BR find ", " search " \fIwords\fR..."
Full-text search with prefix matching.
.TP
.B show \fIid\fR [\-\-raw]
Print one entry in full. Output is raw (content only) when piped.
.TP
.BR copy ", " cp " \fIid\fR"
Put an old entry back on the clipboard.
.TP
.BR pin " \fIid\fR, " unpin " \fIid\fR"
Pinned entries are never pruned and sort first.
.TP
.B rm \fIid\fR...
Delete entries.
.TP
.B purge [\-\-days \fIN\fR | \-\-all] [\-\-pinned\-too] [\-y]
Bulk-delete history. Pins survive unless \-\-pinned\-too is given.
The database is vacuumed afterwards.
.TP
.BR pause ", " resume
Temporarily stop/restart recording (privacy mode).
.TP
.B status
Show daemon state, clipboard backend, and database statistics.
.TP
.B gui
Open the GTK4 search popup: type to filter, click to select, Enter or
double-click copies, Ctrl+P pins, Del deletes, Esc closes. Ctrl+S opens
selection mode for bulk pin/unpin/delete (Ctrl+A selects all).
.TP
.B daemon
Run the clipboard watcher in the foreground.
.TP
.B setup [\-\-hotkey \fIBINDING\fR]
Enable and start the systemd user service; optionally register a GNOME
shortcut for the GUI, e.g. \-\-hotkey '<Control><Alt>v'.
.TP
.B teardown
Remove the service and hotkey. Your history is kept.
.SH PRIVACY
Clipboard contents flagged by password managers (the
x\-kde\-passwordManagerHint MIME hint, set by KeePassXC and others) are
never recorded. Regular expressions in the configuration file can
exclude further content. Use
.B deja pause
before copying anything you do not want remembered.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/deja/deja.db
The history database (SQLite).
.TP
.I ~/.config/deja/config.toml
Optional configuration: max_entries, max_bytes, min_chars,
ignore_patterns (list of regexes).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B DEJA_DB
Override the database path.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR wl-clipboard (1),
.BR xclip (1)
